http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/Fire-in-Srikakulam-destroys-15-houses/article13997336.ece

A major fire accident caused tension among villagers of Antakapalli, Rajam mandal of Srikakulam District in the early hours of Wednesday.According to police, electric short circuit triggered fire and destroyed 15 houses. The villagers were under the grip of panic with blast of five cylinders. Flames spread to other parts destroying Rs.30 lakh worth of property.Fortunately none was injured in the incident. However, the fire accident took away the happiness of Sankranti festival. The district administration revenue, police teams immediately to help victims.Srikakulam Collector P. Lakshmi Narasimham and Srikakulam SP A.S. Khan inquired into the incident. Rajam MLA Kambala Jogulu visited the spot an urged officials to release compensation and essential commodities. He interacted with villagers and learnt about the incident.